Reassigned & Not Reassigned Incidents¶

In [701]:
Filter = df1.groupby('number').apply(lambda x: x['reassignment_count'].unique()) 
z = 0
index = 0
Reassigned = []
Not_Reassigned = []
for key in Filter:
    for val in key:
        val = int(val)
        z +=val
    if z == 0:
        Not_Reassigned.append(Filter.index[index])
    if z != 0:
        Reassigned.append(Filter.index[index])
    z = 0
    index+=1
print("Number of incidents reassigned:", len(Reassigned))
print("Number of incidents not reassigned:", len(Not_Reassigned))
df3 = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(Reassigned, Not_Reassigned)), columns =['Reassigned', 'Not_Reassigned'])
print(df3.head())

Visualizations¶

Locations with number of incidents > 200¶

In [703]:
df5 = df1.copy()
df5['location'] = df5['location'].str.split(" ").str[1]
Filter3 = df.groupby('location').apply(lambda x: x['number'].nunique())
Loc_List= Filter3.index.tolist()
Inc_Num_List = Filter3.tolist()
zip_iterator = zip(Loc_List,Inc_Num_List)
d = dict(zip_iterator)
d2 = {}
for (key, value) in d.items():
    if value>200:
        d2[key] = value
dataF = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(d2, orient = 'index')
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
fig.set_size_inches(18.5, 10.5)
ax.plot(dataF[0], marker = 'o', color = "b", linestyle = "--")
plt.xlabel('Location Numbers', size = 15)
plt.ylabel('Number of incidents', size = 15)
plt.title('Locations with number of incidents > 200', size = 20)
plt.show()

Number of Incidents Reported Each Month¶

In [705]:
df5['opened_at'] =df5['opened_at'].str.split(" ").str[0]
df5['opened_at'] = df5['opened_at'].str.split('/',1).str[1]
Filter3 = df5.groupby('opened_at').apply(lambda x: x['number'].nunique())
Loc_List= Filter3.index.tolist()
Inc_Num_List = Filter3.tolist()
zip_iterator = zip(Loc_List,Inc_Num_List)
d = dict(zip_iterator)
d = OrderedDict(sorted(d.items(), key=lambda x: parse(x[0])))
dataF = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(d, orient = 'index')
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
fig.set_size_inches(18.5, 10.5)
ax.plot(dataF[0], marker = 'o', color = "r", linestyle = "--")

Groups Who Are Assigned > 500 Cases¶

In [706]:
Group_List=[]
count = 0
Temp_L1 = df['incident_state'].tolist()
Temp_L2 = df['assignment_group'].tolist()
for i,j in zip(Temp_L1,Temp_L2):
    if i == "New":
        Group_List.append(j)
        count+=1
    else: 
        continue
d = {}
df10 = pd.DataFrame(Group_List)
df10[0] =df10[0].str.split(" ").str[1]
d = {}
d2 ={}
for i in df10[0]:
    if i in d:
        d[i] = d[i] + 1
    else:
        d[i] = 1
for (key, value) in d.items():
    if value>500:
        d2[key] = value
dataF = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(d2, orient = 'index')
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
fig.set_size_inches(18.5, 10.5)
ax.plot(dataF[0], marker = 'v', color = "orange", linestyle = "--")
plt.xlabel('Group Numbers', size = 15)
plt.ylabel('Number of new incidents', size = 15)
plt.title('Groups who have been assigned more than 500 cases', size = 20)
plt.xticks(size = 12)
plt.yticks(size = 15)
plt.show()

Finding the Average time required to handle an incident report.¶

In [718]:
df9 =df1.copy()
Open_Time=[]
Closed_Time =[]
difference = []
count = 0
Temp_L1 = df9['incident_state'].tolist()
Temp_L2 = df9['opened_at'].tolist()
Temp_L3 = df9['closed_at'].tolist()
for i,j in zip(Temp_L1,Temp_L2):
    if i == "Closed":
        Open_Time.append(j)
        count+=1
    else: 
        continue
for i,j in zip(Temp_L1,Temp_L3):
    if i == "Closed":
        Closed_Time.append(j)
    else: 
        continue

for i,j in zip(Open_Time, Closed_Time):
     i = datetime.datetime.strptime(i, '%d/%m/%Y %H:%M')
     j = datetime.datetime.strptime(j, '%d/%m/%Y %H:%M')
     difference.append(j-i)
print (sum(difference,datetime.timedelta())/len(difference), "          Format: days, hours: minutes: seconds")

13 days, 4:57:39.962377           Format: days, hours: minutes: seconds
